Scrape Internshala Listings
Subtask:
Write Python code to scrape internship listings from Internshala using requests to fetch the page content and BeautifulSoup to parse the HTML. This step will focus on gathering the raw HTML data.

Reasoning: I will write a Python code block to import the necessary libraries, define the Internshala URL, send an HTTP GET request, check the response status, parse the HTML content using BeautifulSoup, and print a portion of the parsed HTML to confirm successful scraping.

import requests
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup

# 1. Define the URL of the Internshala internship listings page
url = 'https://internshala.com/internships'

# 2. Send an HTTP GET request to the URL and store the response
response = requests.get(url)

# 3. Check if the request was successful
if response.status_code == 200:
    print("Successfully fetched the page content. Status code: 200")
    
    # 4. Parse the HTML content of the response using BeautifulSoup
    soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, 'html.parser')
    
    # 5. Print a portion of the parsed HTML to confirm
    print("\n--- Parsed HTML Snippet ---")
    print(soup.prettify()[:500]) # Print first 500 characters of prettified HTML
    print("\nPage Title:", soup.title.string)
else:
    print(f"Failed to fetch page content. Status code: {response.status_code}")
